Add @water{200%ml} and @vegetable stock{1%sachet} to a #pot{} and bring to the boil.

When boiling, remove from the heat, stir in the @couscous{100%g} and pop a lid on the
pot. Leave to the side for ~{8-10%mins} or until ready to serve.

> TIP: If you're in a hurry you can boil the water in your kettle.

Trim the @aubergine{1%unit}, then cut into roughly 2cm pieces. Halve the
@bell pepper{1%unit} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks.
Roughly tear the @basil{20%g} leaves.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a glug of @oil{to taste}. When the oil is
hot, fry the aubergine and pepper for ~{7-9%mins}. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: By stirring only every so often you'll allow the veg to char nicely.

Reduce the heat of the pan to medium-high. Add the @chopped tomato with onion and
garlic{1%pack} and half the torn basil. Cover and simmer for ~{5-7%mins}. Add a splash
of @water{to taste} to loosen the sauce if necessary. Season to taste with salt,
pepper and @sugar{to taste}.

Once everything is ready, fluff up the couscous with a #fork{}. Crumble the
@Greek style cheese{100%g} into small pieces.

Serve the ratatouille on a bed of fluffy couscous. Top with the crumbled Greek style
cheese. Drizzle over a little @balsamic glaze{2%sachets}. Finish with a sprinkling of
torn basil and a pinch of black pepper.